        <p style="font-size: 18px; color: var(--text-muted); line-height: 1.8; margin-bottom: 30px;">Navigating the termination of employment and redundancy procedures in Malta requires a precise understanding of the Department of Industrial and Employment Relations (DIER) regulations. For organizations operating in Malta or expanding into the region, ensuring compliance during workforce restructuring is critical to avoiding costly tribunal claims and reputational damage.</p>

        <p style="font-size: 18px; color: var(--text-muted); line-height: 1.8; margin-bottom: 40px;">At <strong>PrimePath HR</strong>, our dedicated Malta advisory team partners with businesses to seamlessly manage these transitions, mitigating risk while treating employees with dignity and fairness.</p>

        <h2 style="font-size: 28px; margin-bottom: 20px; color: var(--primary-navy);">Key Severance Pay Rules & How We Manage Them</h2>
        <p style="font-size: 16px; color: var(--text-muted); line-height: 1.8; margin-bottom: 20px;">Unlike many other jurisdictions, under Malta employment law, there is <strong>no statutory requirement for employers to pay severance pay</strong> upon redundancy. However, redundancy payouts are often triggered by:</p>

        <ul style="font-size: 16px; color: var(--text-muted); line-height: 1.8; margin-bottom: 20px; padding-left: 20px;">
            <li style="margin-bottom: 10px;"><strong>Employment Contracts:</strong> Specific severance clauses drafted into executive agreements.</li>
            <li style="margin-bottom: 10px;"><strong>Collective Agreements:</strong> Union or sectoral collective agreements dictating redundancy terms.</li>
            <li style="margin-bottom: 10px;"><strong>Company Policy:</strong> Established precedents of paying redundancy packages.</li>
        </ul>

        <div style="background: rgba(0, 180, 216, 0.05); border-left: 4px solid var(--secondary-blue); padding: 25px; border-radius: 0 12px 12px 0; margin-bottom: 50px;">
            <strong style="color: var(--primary-navy); display: block; margin-bottom: 10px; font-size: 18px;"><i class="fas fa-check-circle" style="color: var(--secondary-blue); margin-right: 8px;"></i> PrimePath HR Solution:</strong>
            <p style="font-size: 16px; color: var(--text-muted); margin: 0; line-height: 1.6;">Our legal compliance experts conduct thorough audits of your existing employment contracts and collective agreements to determine your exact financial exposure before any redundancy process begins. We help you draft ironclad contracts that protect your business while remaining highly competitive in the Maltese talent market.</p>
        </div>

        <h2 style="font-size: 28px; margin-bottom: 20px; color: var(--primary-navy);">Mandatory Final Payments: Ensuring Payroll Compliance</h2>
        <p style="font-size: 16px; color: var(--text-muted); line-height: 1.8; margin-bottom: 20px;">While "severance" is not legally mandated by default, employers are legally obligated to settle all other outstanding financial entitlements by the next pay date following the last working day. These include:</p>

        <ol style="font-size: 16px; color: var(--text-muted); line-height: 1.8; margin-bottom: 20px; padding-left: 20px;">
            <li style="margin-bottom: 10px;"><strong>Payment in Lieu of Notice:</strong> Paying full wages if the employee is not required to work their statutory notice period.</li>
            <li style="margin-bottom: 10px;"><strong>Unused Vacation Leave:</strong> Proportional cash-out of accrued annual leave.</li>
            <li style="margin-bottom: 10px;"><strong>Outstanding Wages & Bonuses:</strong> Proportional payment for wages, overtime, and statutory government bonuses.</li>
        </ol>

        <div style="background: rgba(0, 180, 216, 0.05); border-left: 4px solid var(--secondary-blue); padding: 25px; border-radius: 0 12px 12px 0; margin-bottom: 50px;">
            <strong style="color: var(--primary-navy); display: block; margin-bottom: 10px; font-size: 18px;"><i class="fas fa-check-circle" style="color: var(--secondary-blue); margin-right: 8px;"></i> PrimePath HR Solution:</strong>
            <p style="font-size: 16px; color: var(--text-muted); margin: 0; line-height: 1.6;">Calculating final dues accurately under Maltese law can be complex. PrimePath's <strong>Payroll Outsourcing</strong> team handles these intricate final settlement calculations on your behalf, ensuring 100% DIER compliance and zero delays, which protects your company from easily avoidable wage claims.</p>
        </div>

        <h3 style="font-size: 22px; margin-bottom: 15px; color: var(--primary-navy);">Statutory Notice Periods Explained</h3>
        <p style="font-size: 16px; color: var(--text-muted); line-height: 1.8; margin-bottom: 15px;">Notice periods in Malta are calculated based on continuous length of service:</p>
        <ul style="font-size: 16px; color: var(--text-muted); line-height: 1.8; margin-bottom: 50px; padding-left: 20px; list-style-type: square;">
            <li><strong>1 to 6 months:</strong> 1 week notice</li>
            <li><strong>6 months to 2 years:</strong> 2 weeks notice</li>
            <li><strong>2 to 4 years:</strong> 4 weeks notice</li>
            <li><strong>4 to 7 years:</strong> 8 weeks notice</li>
            <li><strong>7+ years:</strong> +1 week per subsequent year (maximum 12 weeks).</li>
        </ul>

        <h2 style="font-size: 28px; margin-bottom: 20px; color: var(--primary-navy);">Re-engagement Rights & Risk Mitigation</h2>
        <ul style="font-size: 16px; color: var(--text-muted); line-height: 1.8; margin-bottom: 20px; padding-left: 20px;">
            <li style="margin-bottom: 10px;"><strong>Right of Re-engagement:</strong> If a redundant role becomes available again within <strong>one year</strong>, it must legally be offered to the former employee first.</li>
            <li style="margin-bottom: 10px;"><strong>Unfair Dismissal Claims:</strong> Employees have <strong>four months</strong> to file a complaint with the Industrial Tribunal if they believe a redundancy was not genuine.</li>
        </ul>

        <div style="background: rgba(0, 180, 216, 0.05); border-left: 4px solid var(--secondary-blue); padding: 25px; border-radius: 0 12px 12px 0; margin-bottom: 50px;">
